 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/1262/exiting-i3-without-mouse-click/?answer=1263#post-id-1263</link><description>You can use dmenu.

    #!/bin/bash
    while [ "$select" != "NO" -a "$select" != "YES" ]; do
        select=$(echo -e 'NO\nYES' | dmenu -nb '#151515' -nf '#999999' -sb '#f00060' -sf '#000000' -fn '-*-*-medium-r-normal-*-*-*-*-*-*-100-*-*' -i -p "You pressed the exit shortcut. Do you really want to exit i3? This will end your X session.")
        [ -z "$select" ] &amp;&amp; exit 0
    done
    [ "$select" = "NO" ] &amp;&amp; exit 0
    i3-msg exit


Save the above code in ~/.i3/exit_menu.sh (don't forget to chmod +x) and change the bindsym to

    bindsym $mod+Shift+e exec ~/.i3/exit_menu.sh

if you don't like the colors or the fonts check 'man dmenu'.</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 Feb 2013 11:29:44 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/1262/exiting-i3-without-mouse-click/?answer=1263#post-id-1263</guid></item><item><title>Comment by Lykos for &lt;p&gt;You can use dmenu.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;#!/bin/bash
while [ "$select" != "NO" -a "$select" != "YES" ]; do
    select=$(echo -e 'NO\nYES' | dmenu -nb '#151515' -nf '#999999' -sb '#f00060' -sf '#000000' -fn '-*-*-medium-r-normal-*-*-*-*-*-*-100-*-*' -i -p "You pressed the exit shortcut. Do you really want to exit i3? This will end your X session.")
    [ -z "$select" ] &amp;amp;&amp;amp; exit 0
done
[ "$select" = "NO" ] &amp;amp;&amp;amp; exit 0
i3-msg exit
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Save the above code in ~/.i3/exit_menu.sh (don't forget to chmod +x) and change the bindsym to&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;bindsym $mod+Shift+e exec ~/.i3/exit_menu.sh
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if you don't like the colors or the fonts check 'man dmenu'.&lt;/p&gt;
</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/1262/exiting-i3-without-mouse-click/?comment=2704#comment-2704</link><description>That's exaclty what I was searching for. Thanks very much!</description><pubDate>Sun, 13 Oct 2013 23:42:13 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/1262/exiting-i3-without-mouse-click/?comment=2704#comment-2704</guid></item><item><title>Comment by Ruben G for &lt;p&gt;You can use dmenu.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;#!/bin/bash
while [ "$select" != "NO" -a "$select" != "YES" ]; do
    select=$(echo -e 'NO\nYES' | dmenu -nb '#151515' -nf '#999999' -sb '#f00060' -sf '#000000' -fn '-*-*-medium-r-normal-*-*-*-*-*-*-100-*-*' -i -p "You pressed the exit shortcut. Do you really want to exit i3? This will end your X session.")
    [ -z "$select" ] &amp;amp;&amp;amp; exit 0
done
[ "$select" = "NO" ] &amp;amp;&amp;amp; exit 0
i3-msg exit
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Save the above code in ~/.i3/exit_menu.sh (don't forget to chmod +x) and change the bindsym to&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;bindsym $mod+Shift+e exec ~/.i3/exit_menu.sh
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if you don't like the colors or the fonts check 'man dmenu'.&lt;/p&gt;
</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/1262/exiting-i3-without-mouse-click/?comment=5527#comment-5527</link><description>inline, no external shell file needed: 

    bindsym $mod+Shift+e exec sh -c '[ $(echo "NO\nYES" | dmenu -sb "#ff6600" -i -p "Really exit i3 X session?") = "YES" ] &amp;&amp; i3-msg exit'
</description><pubDate>Tue, 24 Feb 2015 08:41:57 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/1262/exiting-i3-without-mouse-click/?comment=5527#comment-5527</guid></item><item><title>Comment by sml for &lt;p&gt;You can use dmenu.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;#!/bin/bash
while [ "$select" != "NO" -a "$select" != "YES" ]; do
    select=$(echo -e 'NO\nYES' | dmenu -nb '#151515' -nf '#999999' -sb '#f00060' -sf '#000000' -fn '-*-*-medium-r-normal-*-*-*-*-*-*-100-*-*' -i -p "You pressed the exit shortcut. Do you really want to exit i3? This will end your X session.")
    [ -z "$select" ] &amp;amp;&amp;amp; exit 0
done
[ "$select" = "NO" ] &amp;amp;&amp;amp; exit 0
i3-msg exit
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Save the above code in ~/.i3/exit_menu.sh (don't forget to chmod +x) and change the bindsym to&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;bindsym $mod+Shift+e exec ~/.i3/exit_menu.sh
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if you don't like the colors or the fonts check 'man dmenu'.&lt;/p&gt;
</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/1262/exiting-i3-without-mouse-click/?comment=4241#comment-4241</link><description>I simplified this a bit:

    #!/bin/bash
    [ $(echo -e 'NO\nYES' | dmenu -sb '#ff6600' -fn \
    '-*-*-*-*-*-*-20-*-*-*-*-*-*-*' -i -p "Do you really want to exit? This \
    will end your session.") = "YES" ] &amp;&amp; i3-msg exit
