 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/1262/exiting-i3-without-mouse-click/?answer=3746#post-id-3746</link><description>Hi,
I know, this thread is old, but I found a good solution for me.
In ~/.i3/config I changed the bindsym of exiting to 

    bindsym $mod+Shift+e exec i3-msg exit

That way, it chooses the "Yes, exit i3" path automatically.
</description><pubDate>Tue, 29 Apr 2014 22:35:03 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/1262/exiting-i3-without-mouse-click/?answer=3746#post-id-3746</guid></item><item><title>Comment by Michael for &lt;p&gt;Hi,
I know, this thread is old, but I found a good solution for me.
In ~/.i3/config I changed the bindsym of exiting to &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;bindsym $mod+Shift+e exec i3-msg exit
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That way, it chooses the "Yes, exit i3" path automatically.&lt;/p&gt;
</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/1262/exiting-i3-without-mouse-click/?comment=3877#comment-3877</link><description>Running i3-msg is unnecessary. Just use `bindsym $mod+Shift+e exit`</description><pubDate>Sun, 25 May 2014 18:12:53 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/1262/exiting-i3-without-mouse-click/?comment=3877#comment-3877</guid></item></channel></rss>